WEBVTT

00:00.564 --> 00:01.778
Welcome to Tampa,

00:01.898 --> 00:04.886
land of money, cunny, and
where it's always sunny.

00:05.006 --> 00:06.323
You're interested in heroin.

00:06.443 --> 00:08.007
As a commodity, yes.

00:08.127 --> 00:10.607
This is a business with
which you are familiar?

00:10.727 --> 00:11.908
One of many.

00:12.757 --> 00:13.933
I know you.

00:14.168 --> 00:16.062
So how come we don't
talk anymore?

00:16.183 --> 00:18.342
Mr. O'Banion hopes very much

00:18.589 --> 00:20.559
Cicero becomes
your new home.

00:20.679 --> 00:21.941
And where does that
leave him?

00:22.061 --> 00:23.812
It leaves him
in Chicago.

00:23.932 --> 00:25.556
anything I ask you to do,

00:25.778 --> 00:27.881
you do not discuss it
with anyone.

00:27.926 --> 00:29.733
I never have
and never will.

00:29.853 --> 00:31.931
<i>Enoch Thompson.</i>
You know of him

00:32.051 --> 00:33.065
or you know him?

00:33.185 --> 00:35.710
- Who are you?
- The Bureau of Investigation.

00:36.291 --> 00:37.418
Mr. White,

00:37.538 --> 00:39.300
may I present Miss Daughter Maitland.

00:39.420 --> 00:40.889
Pleased to meet you.

00:41.009 --> 00:42.524
Ready to get rich?

00:42.644 --> 00:44.183
This land is worthless.

00:44.303 --> 00:46.152
You'll have to find
yourselves a new partner.

00:46.272 --> 00:47.413
You told me he was in.

00:47.660 --> 00:49.766
I'm here on new business.

00:50.012 --> 00:53.668
- Where you going, friend?
- As far as you'd like me to take you.

00:53.788 --> 00:55.699
- Henry, cut it out.
- Easy, Henry.

00:55.819 --> 00:57.860
Mind your business, Thompson.

01:00.403 --> 01:02.387
Well, go on, Romeo. Don't let us interrupt.

01:02.507 --> 01:05.120
Enough money and the right connections,

01:05.239 --> 01:07.190
you can do pretty much anything down here.

01:07.310 --> 01:11.137
I've reconsidered. Tell your hillbilly
friend Tucker I'm in.

